==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lauric acid
<hw>Lauric acid</hw> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <def>a white, crystalline
substance, <chform>CH3.(CH2)10.COOH</chform>, resembling palmitic acid,
and obtained from the fruit of the bay tree, and various other vegetable
sources. The sodium salt (<er>sodium lauryl sulfate</er>) is used as a
detergent.</def> <syn><b>Syn. --</b> dodecanoic acid, laurostearic acid,
dodecoic acid.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lauriferous</ent>⟦br⟧
